{"key":"post-9514002","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9514002</id>\n<content>One thing I've found in common with all the pf tek bashers is that they've failed at the easiest tek of all.&amp;nbsp; As you become more experienced, it's the best and quickest way to prove strains after a series of isolations on agar.&amp;nbsp; Once you've proved a great fruiting strain, inoculate grains and use them to inoculate bulk substrates.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;At any rate, 1/2 pint wide mouth jars are in every grocery store I remember walking into in the last ten years.&amp;nbsp; I've never even had to ask the manager to get them.&amp;nbsp; When you move to grains, you'll want regular, not wide mouth jars.&amp;nbsp; The reason is that the smaller lid allows for only half as many contaminants to possibly enter when you open it, since it's half the size.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If necessary, ask your local grocery manager to order you a case or two.&amp;nbsp; Every grocery wholesaler has them in the warehouse.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9514390</next>\n<prev>9513867</prev>\n<first>9513659</first>\n<last>9518743</last>\n<when>1230602674</when>\n<utime>12/30/08 04:04 AM</utime>\n</post>"}